152#define TYPE_CHECK(T, S) \
153 while (false) { \
154 *(static_cast<T* volatile*>(0)) = static_cast<S*>(0); \
155 }
156
188template <class T>
189class Local {
190 public:
191 V8_INLINE Local() : val_(nullptr) {}
192 template <class S>
193 V8_INLINE Local(Local<S> that)
194 : val_(reinterpret_cast<T*>(*that)) {
200 TYPE_CHECK(T, S);
201 }
202
206 V8_INLINE bool IsEmpty() const { return val_ == nullptr; }
207
211 V8_INLINE void Clear() { val_ = nullptr; }
212
213 V8_INLINE T* operator->() const { return val_; }
214
215 V8_INLINE T* operator*() const { return val_; }
216
223 template <class S>
224 V8_INLINE bool operator==(const Local<S>& that) const {
225 internal::Address* a = reinterpret_cast<internal::Address*>(this->val_);
226 internal::Address* b = reinterpret_cast<internal::Address*>(that.val_);
227 if (a == nullptr) return b == nullptr;
228 if (b == nullptr) return false;
229 return *a == *b;
230 }
231
232 template <class S> V8_INLINE bool operator==(
233 const PersistentBase<S>& that) const {
234 internal::Address* a = reinterpret_cast<internal::Address*>(this->val_);
235 internal::Address* b = reinterpret_cast<internal::Address*>(that.val_);
236 if (a == nullptr) return b == nullptr;
237 if (b == nullptr) return false;
238 return *a == *b;
239 }
240
247 template <class S>
248 V8_INLINE bool operator!=(const Local<S>& that) const {
249 return !operator==(that);
250 }
251
252 template <class S> V8_INLINE bool operator!=(
253 const Persistent<S>& that) const {
254 return !operator==(that);
255 }
256
262 template <class S> V8_INLINE static Local<T> Cast(Local<S> that) {
263#ifdef V8_ENABLE_CHECKS
264 // If we're going to perform the type check then we have to check
265 // that the handle isn't empty before doing the checked cast.
266 if (that.IsEmpty()) return Local<T>();
267#endif
268 return Local<T>(T::Cast(*that));
269 }
270
276 template <class S>
277 V8_INLINE Local<S> As() const {
278 return Local<S>::Cast(*this);
279 }
280
286 V8_INLINE static Local<T> New(Isolate* isolate, Local<T> that);
287 V8_INLINE static Local<T> New(Isolate* isolate,
288 const PersistentBase<T>& that);
289 V8_INLINE static Local<T> New(Isolate* isolate,
290 const TracedReferenceBase<T>& that);
291
292 private:
293 friend class Utils;
294 template<class F> friend class Eternal;
295 template<class F> friend class PersistentBase;
296 template<class F, class M> friend class Persistent;
297 template<class F> friend class Local;
298 template <class F>
299 friend class MaybeLocal;
300 template<class F> friend class FunctionCallbackInfo;
301 template<class F> friend class PropertyCallbackInfo;
302 friend class String;
303 friend class Object;
304 friend class Context;
305 friend class Isolate;
306 friend class Private;
307 template<class F> friend class internal::CustomArguments;
308 friend Local<Primitive> Undefined(Isolate* isolate);
309 friend Local<Primitive> Null(Isolate* isolate);
310 friend Local<Boolean> True(Isolate* isolate);
311 friend Local<Boolean> False(Isolate* isolate);
312 friend class HandleScope;
313 friend class EscapableHandleScope;
314 template <class F1, class F2, class F3>
315 friend class PersistentValueMapBase;
316 template<class F1, class F2> friend class PersistentValueVector;
317 template <class F>
318 friend class ReturnValue;
319 template <class F>
320 friend class Traced;
321 template <class F>
322 friend class TracedGlobal;
323 template <class F>
324 friend class TracedReferenceBase;
325 template <class F>
326 friend class TracedReference;
327
328 explicit V8_INLINE Local(T* that) : val_(that) {}
329 V8_INLINE static Local<T> New(Isolate* isolate, T* that);
330 T* val_;
331};

351template <class T>
352class MaybeLocal {
353 public:
354 V8_INLINE MaybeLocal() : val_(nullptr) {}
355 template <class S>
356 V8_INLINE MaybeLocal(Local<S> that)
357 : val_(reinterpret_cast<T*>(*that)) {
358 TYPE_CHECK(T, S);
359 }
360
361 V8_INLINE bool IsEmpty() const { return val_ == nullptr; }
362
367 template <class S>
368 V8_WARN_UNUSED_RESULT V8_INLINE bool ToLocal(Local<S>* out) const {
369 out->val_ = IsEmpty() ? nullptr : this->val_;
370 return !IsEmpty();
371 }
372
377 V8_INLINE Local<T> ToLocalChecked();
378
383 template <class S>
384 V8_INLINE Local<S> FromMaybe(Local<S> default_value) const {
385 return IsEmpty() ? default_value : Local<S>(val_);
386 }
387
388 private:
389 T* val_;
390};

396template <class T> class Eternal {
397 public:
398 V8_INLINE Eternal() : val_(nullptr) {}
399 template <class S>
400 V8_INLINE Eternal(Isolate* isolate, Local<S> handle) : val_(nullptr) {
401 Set(isolate, handle);
402 }
403 // Can only be safely called if already set.
404 V8_INLINE Local<T> Get(Isolate* isolate) const;
405 V8_INLINE bool IsEmpty() const { return val_ == nullptr; }
406 template<class S> V8_INLINE void Set(Isolate* isolate, Local<S> handle);
407
408 private:
409 T* val_;
410};

413static const int kInternalFieldsInWeakCallback = 2;
414static const int kEmbedderFieldsInWeakCallback = 2;
415
416template <typename T>
417class WeakCallbackInfo {
418 public:
419 typedef void (*Callback)(const WeakCallbackInfo<T>& data);
420
421 WeakCallbackInfo(Isolate* isolate, T* parameter,
422 void* embedder_fields[kEmbedderFieldsInWeakCallback],
423 Callback* callback)
424 : isolate_(isolate), parameter_(parameter), callback_(callback) {
425 for (int i = 0; i < kEmbedderFieldsInWeakCallback; ++i) {
426 embedder_fields_[i] = embedder_fields[i];
427 }
428 }
429
430 V8_INLINE Isolate* GetIsolate() const { return isolate_; }
431 V8_INLINE T* GetParameter() const { return parameter_; }
432 V8_INLINE void* GetInternalField(int index) const;
433
434 // When first called, the embedder MUST Reset() the Global which triggered the
435 // callback. The Global itself is unusable for anything else. No v8 other api
436 // calls may be called in the first callback. Should additional work be
437 // required, the embedder must set a second pass callback, which will be
438 // called after all the initial callbacks are processed.
439 // Calling SetSecondPassCallback on the second pass will immediately crash.
440 void SetSecondPassCallback(Callback callback) const { *callback_ = callback; }
441
442 private:
443 Isolate* isolate_;
444 T* parameter_;
445 Callback* callback_;
446 void* embedder_fields_[kEmbedderFieldsInWeakCallback];
447};
448
449
450// kParameter will pass a void* parameter back to the callback, kInternalFields
451// will pass the first two internal fields back to the callback, kFinalizer
452// will pass a void* parameter back, but is invoked before the object is
453// actually collected, so it can be resurrected. In the last case, it is not
454// possible to request a second pass callback.
455enum class WeakCallbackType { kParameter, kInternalFields, kFinalizer };
456
470template <class T> class PersistentBase {
471 public:
476 V8_INLINE void Reset();
481 template <class S>
482 V8_INLINE void Reset(Isolate* isolate, const Local<S>& other);
483
488 template <class S>
489 V8_INLINE void Reset(Isolate* isolate, const PersistentBase<S>& other);
490
491 V8_INLINE bool IsEmpty() const { return val_ == nullptr; }
492 V8_INLINE void Empty() { val_ = 0; }
493
494 V8_INLINE Local<T> Get(Isolate* isolate) const {
495 return Local<T>::New(isolate, *this);
496 }
497
498 template <class S>
499 V8_INLINE bool operator==(const PersistentBase<S>& that) const {
500 internal::Address* a = reinterpret_cast<internal::Address*>(this->val_);
501 internal::Address* b = reinterpret_cast<internal::Address*>(that.val_);
502 if (a == nullptr) return b == nullptr;
503 if (b == nullptr) return false;
504 return *a == *b;
505 }
506
507 template <class S>
508 V8_INLINE bool operator==(const Local<S>& that) const {
509 internal::Address* a = reinterpret_cast<internal::Address*>(this->val_);
510 internal::Address* b = reinterpret_cast<internal::Address*>(that.val_);
511 if (a == nullptr) return b == nullptr;
512 if (b == nullptr) return false;
513 return *a == *b;
514 }
515
516 template <class S>
517 V8_INLINE bool operator!=(const PersistentBase<S>& that) const {
518 return !operator==(that);
519 }
520
521 template <class S>
522 V8_INLINE bool operator!=(const Local<S>& that) const {
523 return !operator==(that);
524 }
525
533 template <typename P>
534 V8_INLINE void SetWeak(P* parameter,
535 typename WeakCallbackInfo<P>::Callback callback,
536 WeakCallbackType type);
537
545 V8_INLINE void SetWeak();
546
547 template<typename P>
548 V8_INLINE P* ClearWeak();
549
550 // TODO(dcarney): remove this.
551 V8_INLINE void ClearWeak() { ClearWeak<void>(); }
552
559 V8_INLINE void AnnotateStrongRetainer(const char* label);
560
562 V8_INLINE bool IsWeak() const;
563
567 V8_INLINE void SetWrapperClassId(uint16_t class_id);
568
573 V8_INLINE uint16_t WrapperClassId() const;
574
575 PersistentBase(const PersistentBase& other) = delete; // NOLINT
576 void operator=(const PersistentBase&) = delete;
577
578 private:
579 friend class Isolate;
580 friend class Utils;
581 template<class F> friend class Local;
582 template<class F1, class F2> friend class Persistent;
583 template <class F>
584 friend class Global;
585 template<class F> friend class PersistentBase;
586 template<class F> friend class ReturnValue;
587 template <class F1, class F2, class F3>
588 friend class PersistentValueMapBase;
589 template<class F1, class F2> friend class PersistentValueVector;
590 friend class Object;
591
592 explicit V8_INLINE PersistentBase(T* val) : val_(val) {}
593 V8_INLINE static T* New(Isolate* isolate, T* that);
594
595 T* val_;
596};

605template<class T>
606class NonCopyablePersistentTraits {
607 public:
608 typedef Persistent<T, NonCopyablePersistentTraits<T> > NonCopyablePersistent;
609 static const bool kResetInDestructor = false;
610 template<class S, class M>
611 V8_INLINE static void Copy(const Persistent<S, M>& source,
612 NonCopyablePersistent* dest) {
613 Uncompilable<Object>();
614 }
615 // TODO(dcarney): come up with a good compile error here.
616 template<class O> V8_INLINE static void Uncompilable() {
617 TYPE_CHECK(O, Primitive);
618 }
619};

626template<class T>
627struct CopyablePersistentTraits {
628 typedef Persistent<T, CopyablePersistentTraits<T> > CopyablePersistent;
629 static const bool kResetInDestructor = true;
630 template<class S, class M>
631 static V8_INLINE void Copy(const Persistent<S, M>& source,
632 CopyablePersistent* dest) {
633 // do nothing, just allow copy
634 }
635};

646template <class T, class M> class Persistent : public PersistentBase<T> {
647 public:
651 V8_INLINE Persistent() : PersistentBase<T>(nullptr) {}
657 template <class S>
658 V8_INLINE Persistent(Isolate* isolate, Local<S> that)
659 : PersistentBase<T>(PersistentBase<T>::New(isolate, *that)) {
660 TYPE_CHECK(T, S);
661 }
667 template <class S, class M2>
668 V8_INLINE Persistent(Isolate* isolate, const Persistent<S, M2>& that)
669 : PersistentBase<T>(PersistentBase<T>::New(isolate, *that)) {
670 TYPE_CHECK(T, S);
671 }
678 V8_INLINE Persistent(const Persistent& that) : PersistentBase<T>(nullptr) {
679 Copy(that);
680 }
681 template <class S, class M2>
682 V8_INLINE Persistent(const Persistent<S, M2>& that) : PersistentBase<T>(0) {
683 Copy(that);
684 }
685 V8_INLINE Persistent& operator=(const Persistent& that) {
686 Copy(that);
687 return *this;
688 }
689 template <class S, class M2>
690 V8_INLINE Persistent& operator=(const Persistent<S, M2>& that) { // NOLINT
691 Copy(that);
692 return *this;
693 }
699 V8_INLINE ~Persistent() {
700 if (M::kResetInDestructor) this->Reset();
701 }
702
703 // TODO(dcarney): this is pretty useless, fix or remove
704 template <class S>
705 V8_INLINE static Persistent<T>& Cast(const Persistent<S>& that) { // NOLINT
706#ifdef V8_ENABLE_CHECKS
707 // If we're going to perform the type check then we have to check
708 // that the handle isn't empty before doing the checked cast.
709 if (!that.IsEmpty()) T::Cast(*that);
710#endif
711 return reinterpret_cast<Persistent<T>&>(const_cast<Persistent<S>&>(that));
712 }
713
714 // TODO(dcarney): this is pretty useless, fix or remove
715 template <class S>
716 V8_INLINE Persistent<S>& As() const { // NOLINT
717 return Persistent<S>::Cast(*this);
718 }
719
720 private:
721 friend class Isolate;
722 friend class Utils;
723 template<class F> friend class Local;
724 template<class F1, class F2> friend class Persistent;
725 template<class F> friend class ReturnValue;
726
727 explicit V8_INLINE Persistent(T* that) : PersistentBase<T>(that) {}
728 V8_INLINE T* operator*() const { return this->val_; }
729 template<class S, class M2>
730 V8_INLINE void Copy(const Persistent<S, M2>& that);
731};

794

798 V8_INLINE T* operator*() const { return this->val_; }

827template <typename T>
828class TracedReferenceBase {
829 public:
834 bool IsEmpty() const { return val_ == nullptr; }
835
840 V8_INLINE void Reset();
841
845 Local<T> Get(Isolate* isolate) const { return Local<T>::New(isolate, *this); }
846
847 template <class S>
848 V8_INLINE bool operator==(const TracedReferenceBase<S>& that) const {
849 internal::Address* a = reinterpret_cast<internal::Address*>(val_);
850 internal::Address* b = reinterpret_cast<internal::Address*>(that.val_);
851 if (a == nullptr) return b == nullptr;
852 if (b == nullptr) return false;
853 return *a == *b;
854 }
855
856 template <class S>
857 V8_INLINE bool operator==(const Local<S>& that) const {
858 internal::Address* a = reinterpret_cast<internal::Address*>(val_);
859 internal::Address* b = reinterpret_cast<internal::Address*>(that.val_);
860 if (a == nullptr) return b == nullptr;
861 if (b == nullptr) return false;
862 return *a == *b;
863 }
864
865 template <class S>
866 V8_INLINE bool operator!=(const TracedReferenceBase<S>& that) const {
867 return !operator==(that);
868 }
869
870 template <class S>
871 V8_INLINE bool operator!=(const Local<S>& that) const {
872 return !operator==(that);
873 }
874
878 V8_INLINE void SetWrapperClassId(uint16_t class_id);
879
884 V8_INLINE uint16_t WrapperClassId() const;
885
886 template <class S>
887 V8_INLINE TracedReferenceBase<S>& As() const {
888 return reinterpret_cast<TracedReferenceBase<S>&>(
889 const_cast<TracedReferenceBase<T>&>(*this));
890 }
891
892 private:
893 enum DestructionMode { kWithDestructor, kWithoutDestructor };
894
898 TracedReferenceBase() = default;
899
900 V8_INLINE static T* New(Isolate* isolate, T* that, void* slot,
901 DestructionMode destruction_mode);
902
903 T* val_ = nullptr;
904
905 friend class EmbedderHeapTracer;
906 template <typename F>
907 friend class Local;
908 friend class Object;
909 template <typename F>
910 friend class TracedGlobal;

1214 template<class F> friend class Local;

1216 // Object::GetInternalField and Context::GetEmbedderData use CreateHandle with
1217 // a HeapObject in their shortcuts.
1218 friend class Object;
1219 friend class Context;
1220};

1340class ScriptOriginOptions {
1341 public:
1342 V8_INLINE ScriptOriginOptions(bool is_shared_cross_origin = false,
1343 bool is_opaque = false, bool is_wasm = false,
1344 bool is_module = false)
1345 : flags_((is_shared_cross_origin ? kIsSharedCrossOrigin : 0) |
1346 (is_wasm ? kIsWasm : 0) | (is_opaque ? kIsOpaque : 0) |
1347 (is_module ? kIsModule : 0)) {}
1348 V8_INLINE ScriptOriginOptions(int flags)
1349 : flags_(flags &
1350 (kIsSharedCrossOrigin | kIsOpaque | kIsWasm | kIsModule)) {}
1351
1352 bool IsSharedCrossOrigin() const {
1353 return (flags_ & kIsSharedCrossOrigin) != 0;
1354 }
1355 bool IsOpaque() const { return (flags_ & kIsOpaque) != 0; }
1356 bool IsWasm() const { return (flags_ & kIsWasm) != 0; }
1357 bool IsModule() const { return (flags_ & kIsModule) != 0; }
1358
1359 int Flags() const { return flags_; }
1360
1361 private:
1362 enum {
1363 kIsSharedCrossOrigin = 1,
1364 kIsOpaque = 1 << 1,
1365 kIsWasm = 1 << 2,
1366 kIsModule = 1 << 3
1367 };
1368 const int flags_;
1369};

1622class V8_EXPORT ScriptCompiler {
1623 public:
1631 struct V8_EXPORT CachedData {
1632 enum BufferPolicy {
1633 BufferNotOwned,
1634 BufferOwned
1635 };
1636
1637 CachedData()
1638 : data(nullptr),
1639 length(0),
1640 rejected(false),
1641 buffer_policy(BufferNotOwned) {}
1642
1643 // If buffer_policy is BufferNotOwned, the caller keeps the ownership of
1644 // data and guarantees that it stays alive until the CachedData object is
1645 // destroyed. If the policy is BufferOwned, the given data will be deleted
1646 // (with delete[]) when the CachedData object is destroyed.
1647 CachedData(const uint8_t* data, int length,
1648 BufferPolicy buffer_policy = BufferNotOwned);
1649 ~CachedData();
1650 // TODO(marja): Async compilation; add constructors which take a callback
1651 // which will be called when V8 no longer needs the data.
1652 const uint8_t* data;
1653 int length;
1654 bool rejected;
1655 BufferPolicy buffer_policy;
1656
1657 // Prevent copying.
1658 CachedData(const CachedData&) = delete;
1659 CachedData& operator=(const CachedData&) = delete;
1660 };
1661
1665 class Source {
1666 public:
1667 // Source takes ownership of CachedData.
1668 V8_INLINE Source(Local<String> source_string, const ScriptOrigin& origin,
1669 CachedData* cached_data = nullptr);
1670 V8_INLINE Source(Local<String> source_string,
1671 CachedData* cached_data = nullptr);
1672 V8_INLINE ~Source();
1673
1674 // Ownership of the CachedData or its buffers is *not* transferred to the
1675 // caller. The CachedData object is alive as long as the Source object is
1676 // alive.
1677 V8_INLINE const CachedData* GetCachedData() const;
1678
1679 V8_INLINE const ScriptOriginOptions& GetResourceOptions() const;
1680
1681 // Prevent copying.
1682 Source(const Source&) = delete;
1683 Source& operator=(const Source&) = delete;
1684
1685 private:
1686 friend class ScriptCompiler;
1687
1688 Local<String> source_string;
1689
1690 // Origin information
1691 Local<Value> resource_name;
1692 Local<Integer> resource_line_offset;
1693 Local<Integer> resource_column_offset;
1694 ScriptOriginOptions resource_options;
1695 Local<Value> source_map_url;
1696 Local<PrimitiveArray> host_defined_options;
1697
1698 // Cached data from previous compilation (if a kConsume*Cache flag is
1699 // set), or hold newly generated cache data (kProduce*Cache flags) are
1700 // set when calling a compile method.
1701 CachedData* cached_data;
1702 };

2180// A StateTag represents a possible state of the VM.
2181enum StateTag {
2182 JS,
2183 GC,
2184 PARSER,
2185 BYTECODE_COMPILER,
2186 COMPILER,
2187 OTHER,
2188 EXTERNAL,
2189 IDLE
2190};
2191
2192// A RegisterState represents the current state of registers used
2193// by the sampling profiler API.
2194struct RegisterState {
2195 RegisterState() : pc(nullptr), sp(nullptr), fp(nullptr), lr(nullptr) {}
2196 void* pc; // Instruction pointer.
2197 void* sp; // Stack pointer.
2198 void* fp; // Frame pointer.
2199 void* lr; // Link register (or nullptr on platforms without a link register).
2200};
2201
2202// The output structure filled up by GetStackSample API function.
2203struct SampleInfo {
2204 size_t frames_count; // Number of frames collected.
2205 StateTag vm_state; // Current VM state.
2206 void* external_callback_entry; // External callback address if VM is
2207 // executing an external callback.
2208 void* top_context; // Incumbent native context address.
2209};

3577 // Implements CreateDataProperty (ECMA-262, 7.3.4).
3578 //
3579 // Defines a configurable, writable, enumerable property with the given value
3580 // on the object unless the property already exists and is not configurable
3581 // or the object is not extensible.

3602 //
3603 // The defineProperty function is used to add an own property or
3604 // update the attributes of an existing own property of an object.
3605 //
3606 // Both data and accessor descriptors can be used.
3607 //
3608 // In general, CreateDataProperty is faster, however, does not allow
3609 // for specifying attributes or an accessor descriptor.

4105template<typename T>
4106class ReturnValue {
4107 public:
4108 template <class S> V8_INLINE ReturnValue(const ReturnValue<S>& that)
4109 : value_(that.value_) {
4110 TYPE_CHECK(T, S);
4111 }
4112 // Local setters
4113 template <typename S>
4114 V8_INLINE void Set(const Global<S>& handle);
4115 template <typename S>
4116 V8_INLINE void Set(const TracedReferenceBase<S>& handle);
4117 template <typename S>
4118 V8_INLINE void Set(const Local<S> handle);
4119 // Fast primitive setters
4120 V8_INLINE void Set(bool value);
4121 V8_INLINE void Set(double i);
4122 V8_INLINE void Set(int32_t i);
4123 V8_INLINE void Set(uint32_t i);
4124 // Fast JS primitive setters
4125 V8_INLINE void SetNull();
4126 V8_INLINE void SetUndefined();
4127 V8_INLINE void SetEmptyString();
4128 // Convenience getter for Isolate
4129 V8_INLINE Isolate* GetIsolate() const;
4130
4131 // Pointer setter: Uncompilable to prevent inadvertent misuse.
4132 template <typename S>
4133 V8_INLINE void Set(S* whatever);
4134
4135 // Getter. Creates a new Local<> so it comes with a certain performance
4136 // hit. If the ReturnValue was not yet set, this will return the undefined
4137 // value.
4138 V8_INLINE Local<Value> Get() const;
4139
4140 private:
4141 template<class F> friend class ReturnValue;
4142 template<class F> friend class FunctionCallbackInfo;
4143 template<class F> friend class PropertyCallbackInfo;
4144 template <class F, class G, class H>
4145 friend class PersistentValueMapBase;
4146 V8_INLINE void SetInternal(internal::Address value) { *value_ = value; }
4147 V8_INLINE internal::Address GetDefaultValue();
4148 V8_INLINE explicit ReturnValue(internal::Address* slot);
4149 internal::Address* value_;
4150};

6443struct NamedPropertyHandlerConfiguration {
6444 NamedPropertyHandlerConfiguration(
6445 GenericNamedPropertyGetterCallback getter,
6446 GenericNamedPropertySetterCallback setter,
6447 GenericNamedPropertyQueryCallback query,
6448 GenericNamedPropertyDeleterCallback deleter,
6449 GenericNamedPropertyEnumeratorCallback enumerator,
6450 GenericNamedPropertyDefinerCallback definer,
6451 GenericNamedPropertyDescriptorCallback descriptor,
6452 Local<Value> data = Local<Value>(),
6453 PropertyHandlerFlags flags = PropertyHandlerFlags::kNone)
6454 : getter(getter),
6455 setter(setter),
6456 query(query),
6457 deleter(deleter),
6458 enumerator(enumerator),
6459 definer(definer),
6460 descriptor(descriptor),
6461 data(data),
6462 flags(flags) {}
6463
6464 NamedPropertyHandlerConfiguration(
6466 GenericNamedPropertyGetterCallback getter = nullptr,
6467 GenericNamedPropertySetterCallback setter = nullptr,
6468 GenericNamedPropertyQueryCallback query = nullptr,
6469 GenericNamedPropertyDeleterCallback deleter = nullptr,
6470 GenericNamedPropertyEnumeratorCallback enumerator = nullptr,
6471 Local<Value> data = Local<Value>(),
6472 PropertyHandlerFlags flags = PropertyHandlerFlags::kNone)
6473 : getter(getter),
6474 setter(setter),
6475 query(query),
6476 deleter(deleter),
6477 enumerator(enumerator),
6478 definer(nullptr),
6479 descriptor(nullptr),
6480 data(data),
6481 flags(flags) {}
6482
6483 NamedPropertyHandlerConfiguration(
6484 GenericNamedPropertyGetterCallback getter,
6485 GenericNamedPropertySetterCallback setter,
6486 GenericNamedPropertyDescriptorCallback descriptor,
6487 GenericNamedPropertyDeleterCallback deleter,
6488 GenericNamedPropertyEnumeratorCallback enumerator,
6489 GenericNamedPropertyDefinerCallback definer,
6490 Local<Value> data = Local<Value>(),
6491 PropertyHandlerFlags flags = PropertyHandlerFlags::kNone)
6492 : getter(getter),
6493 setter(setter),
6494 query(nullptr),
6495 deleter(deleter),
6496 enumerator(enumerator),
6497 definer(definer),
6498 descriptor(descriptor),
6499 data(data),
6500 flags(flags) {}
6501
6502 GenericNamedPropertyGetterCallback getter;
6503 GenericNamedPropertySetterCallback setter;
6504 GenericNamedPropertyQueryCallback query;
6505 GenericNamedPropertyDeleterCallback deleter;
6506 GenericNamedPropertyEnumeratorCallback enumerator;
6507 GenericNamedPropertyDefinerCallback definer;

6509 Local<Value> data;

6511};

6567 definer(definer),
6568 descriptor(descriptor),
6569 data(data),
6570 flags(flags) {}
6571
6572 IndexedPropertyGetterCallback getter;
6573 IndexedPropertySetterCallback setter;
6574 IndexedPropertyQueryCallback query;
6575 IndexedPropertyDeleterCallback deleter;
6576 IndexedPropertyEnumeratorCallback enumerator;
6577 IndexedPropertyDefinerCallback definer;
6578 IndexedPropertyDescriptorCallback descriptor;
6579 Local<Value> data;
6580 PropertyHandlerFlags flags;
6581};

7556
7562struct JitCodeEvent {
7563 enum EventType {
7564 CODE_ADDED,
7565 CODE_MOVED,
7566 CODE_REMOVED,
7567 CODE_ADD_LINE_POS_INFO,
7568 CODE_START_LINE_INFO_RECORDING,
7569 CODE_END_LINE_INFO_RECORDING
7570 };
7571 // Definition of the code position type. The "POSITION" type means the place
7572 // in the source code which are of interest when making stack traces to
7573 // pin-point the source location of a stack frame as close as possible.
7574 // The "STATEMENT_POSITION" means the place at the beginning of each
7575 // statement, and is used to indicate possible break locations.
7576 enum PositionType { POSITION, STATEMENT_POSITION };
7577
7578 // There are two different kinds of JitCodeEvents, one for JIT code generated
7579 // by the optimizing compiler, and one for byte code generated for the
7580 // interpreter. For JIT_CODE events, the |code_start| member of the event
7581 // points to the beginning of jitted assembly code, while for BYTE_CODE
7582 // events, |code_start| points to the first bytecode of the interpreted
7583 // function.
7584 enum CodeType { BYTE_CODE, JIT_CODE };
7585
7586 // Type of event.
7587 EventType type;
7588 CodeType code_type;
7589 // Start of the instructions.
7590 void* code_start;
7591 // Size of the instructions.
7592 size_t code_len;
7593 // Script info for CODE_ADDED event.
7594 Local<UnboundScript> script;
7595 // User-defined data for *_LINE_INFO_* event. It's used to hold the source
7596 // code line information which is returned from the
7597 // CODE_START_LINE_INFO_RECORDING event. And it's passed to subsequent
7598 // CODE_ADD_LINE_POS_INFO and CODE_END_LINE_INFO_RECORDING events.
7599 void* user_data;
7600
7601 struct name_t {
7602 // Name of the object associated with the code, note that the string is not
7603 // zero-terminated.
7604 const char* str;
7605 // Number of chars in str.
7606 size_t len;
7607 };
7608
7609 struct line_info_t {
7610 // PC offset
7611 size_t offset;
7612 // Code position
7613 size_t pos;
7614 // The position type.
7615 PositionType position_type;
7616 };
7617
7618 struct wasm_source_info_t {
7619 // Source file name.
7620 const char* filename;
7621 // Length of filename.
7622 size_t filename_size;
7623 // Line number table, which maps offsets of JITted code to line numbers of
7624 // source file.
7625 const line_info_t* line_number_table;
7626 // Number of entries in the line number table.
7627 size_t line_number_table_size;
7628 };
7629
7630 wasm_source_info_t* wasm_source_info;
7631
7632 union {
7633 // Only valid for CODE_ADDED.
7634 struct name_t name;
7635
7636 // Only valid for CODE_ADD_LINE_POS_INFO
7637 struct line_info_t line_info;
7638
7639 // New location of instructions. Only valid for CODE_MOVED.
7640 void* new_code_start;
7641 };
7642
7643 Isolate* isolate;
7644};
7645
7651enum RAILMode : unsigned {
7652 // Response performance mode: In this mode very low virtual machine latency
7653 // is provided. V8 will try to avoid JavaScript execution interruptions.
7654 // Throughput may be throttled.
7655 PERFORMANCE_RESPONSE,
7656 // Animation performance mode: In this mode low virtual machine latency is
7657 // provided. V8 will try to avoid as many JavaScript execution interruptions
7658 // as possible. Throughput may be throttled. This is the default mode.
7659 PERFORMANCE_ANIMATION,
7660 // Idle performance mode: The embedder is idle. V8 can complete deferred work
7661 // in this mode.
7662 PERFORMANCE_IDLE,
7663 // Load performance mode: In this mode high throughput is provided. V8 may
7664 // turn off latency optimizations.
7665 PERFORMANCE_LOAD
7666};
7667

7672 kJitCodeEventDefault = 0,
7673 // Generate callbacks for already existent code.
7674 kJitCodeEventEnumExisting = 1
7675};

7881 * Should only be used in testing code.

7886 * Called by the embedder to signal newly allocated or freed memory. Not bound
7887 * to tracing phases. Embedders should trade off when increments are reported
7888 * as V8 may consult global heuristics on whether to trigger garbage
7889 * collection on this change.

7900 protected:

9238 Isolate& operator=(const Isolate&) = delete;
9239 // Deleting operator new and delete here is allowed as ctor and dtor is also
9240 // deleted.
9241 void* operator new(size_t size) = delete;
9242 void* operator new[](size_t size) = delete;
9243 void operator delete(void*, size_t) = delete;
9244 void operator delete[](void*, size_t) = delete;
9245
9246 private:
9247 template <class K, class V, class Traits>
9248 friend class PersistentValueMapBase;
9249
9250 internal::Address* GetDataFromSnapshotOnce(size_t index);
9251 void ReportExternalAllocationLimitReached();
9252 void CheckMemoryPressure();
9253};

9642template <class T>
9643class Maybe {
9644 public:
9645 V8_INLINE bool IsNothing() const { return !has_value_; }
9646 V8_INLINE bool IsJust() const { return has_value_; }
9647
9651 V8_INLINE T ToChecked() const { return FromJust(); }
9652
9657 V8_INLINE void Check() const {
9658 if (V8_UNLIKELY(!IsJust())) V8::FromJustIsNothing();
9659 }
9660
9665 V8_WARN_UNUSED_RESULT V8_INLINE bool To(T* out) const {
9666 if (V8_LIKELY(IsJust())) *out = value_;
9667 return IsJust();
9668 }
9669
9674 V8_INLINE T FromJust() const {
9675 if (V8_UNLIKELY(!IsJust())) V8::FromJustIsNothing();
9676 return value_;
9677 }
9678
9683 V8_INLINE T FromMaybe(const T& default_value) const {
9684 return has_value_ ? value_ : default_value;
9685 }
9686
9687 V8_INLINE bool operator==(const Maybe& other) const {
9688 return (IsJust() == other.IsJust()) &&
9689 (!IsJust() || FromJust() == other.FromJust());
9690 }
9691
9692 V8_INLINE bool operator!=(const Maybe& other) const {
9693 return !operator==(other);
9694 }
9695
9696 private:
9697 Maybe() : has_value_(false) {}
9698 explicit Maybe(const T& t) : has_value_(true), value_(t) {}
9699
9700 bool has_value_;
9701 T value_;
9702
9703 template <class U>
9704 friend Maybe<U> Nothing();
9705 template <class U>
9706 friend Maybe<U> Just(const U& u);
9707};
9708
9709template <class T>
9710inline Maybe<T> Nothing() {
9711 return Maybe<T>();
9712}
9713
9714template <class T>
9715inline Maybe<T> Just(const T& t) {
9716 return Maybe<T>(t);
9717}
9718
9719// A template specialization of Maybe<T> for the case of T = void.
9720template <>
9721class Maybe<void> {
9722 public:
9723 V8_INLINE bool IsNothing() const { return !is_valid_; }
9724 V8_INLINE bool IsJust() const { return is_valid_; }
9725
9726 V8_INLINE bool operator==(const Maybe& other) const {
9727 return IsJust() == other.IsJust();
9728 }
9729
9730 V8_INLINE bool operator!=(const Maybe& other) const {
9731 return !operator==(other);
9732 }
9733
9734 private:
9735 struct JustTag {};
9736
9737 Maybe() : is_valid_(false) {}
9738 explicit Maybe(JustTag) : is_valid_(true) {}
9739
9740 bool is_valid_;
9741
9742 template <class U>
9743 friend Maybe<U> Nothing();
9744 friend Maybe<void> JustVoid();
9745};
9746
9747inline Maybe<void> JustVoid() { return Maybe<void>(Maybe<void>::JustTag()); }

10404
10405template <class T>
10406Local<T> Local<T>::New(Isolate* isolate, Local<T> that) {
10407 return New(isolate, that.val_);
10408}
10409
10410template <class T>
10411Local<T> Local<T>::New(Isolate* isolate, const PersistentBase<T>& that) {
10412 return New(isolate, that.val_);
10413}
10414
10415template <class T>
10416Local<T> Local<T>::New(Isolate* isolate, const TracedReferenceBase<T>& that) {
10417 return New(isolate, that.val_);
10418}
10419
10420template <class T>
10421Local<T> Local<T>::New(Isolate* isolate, T* that) {
10422 if (that == nullptr) return Local<T>();
10423 T* that_ptr = that;
10424 internal::Address* p = reinterpret_cast<internal::Address*>(that_ptr);
10425 return Local<T>(reinterpret_cast<T*>(HandleScope::CreateHandle(
10426 reinterpret_cast<internal::Isolate*>(isolate), *p)));
10427}
10428
10429
10430template<class T>
10431template<class S>
10432void Eternal<T>::Set(Isolate* isolate, Local<S> handle) {
10433 TYPE_CHECK(T, S);
10434 val_ = reinterpret_cast<T*>(
10435 V8::Eternalize(isolate, reinterpret_cast<Value*>(*handle)));
10436}
10437
10438template <class T>
10439Local<T> Eternal<T>::Get(Isolate* isolate) const {
10440 // The eternal handle will never go away, so as with the roots, we don't even
10441 // need to open a handle.
10442 return Local<T>(val_);
10443}
10444
10445
10446template <class T>
10447Local<T> MaybeLocal<T>::ToLocalChecked() {
10448 if (V8_UNLIKELY(val_ == nullptr)) V8::ToLocalEmpty();
10449 return Local<T>(val_);
10450}
10451
10452
10453template <class T>
10454void* WeakCallbackInfo<T>::GetInternalField(int index) const {
10455#ifdef V8_ENABLE_CHECKS
10456 if (index < 0 || index >= kEmbedderFieldsInWeakCallback) {
10457 V8::InternalFieldOutOfBounds(index);
10458 }
10459#endif
10460 return embedder_fields_[index];
10461}
10462
10463
10464template <class T>
10465T* PersistentBase<T>::New(Isolate* isolate, T* that) {
10466 if (that == nullptr) return nullptr;
10467 internal::Address* p = reinterpret_cast<internal::Address*>(that);
10468 return reinterpret_cast<T*>(
10469 V8::GlobalizeReference(reinterpret_cast<internal::Isolate*>(isolate),
10470 p));
10471}
10472
10473
10474template <class T, class M>
10475template <class S, class M2>
10476void Persistent<T, M>::Copy(const Persistent<S, M2>& that) {
10477 TYPE_CHECK(T, S);
10478 this->Reset();
10479 if (that.IsEmpty()) return;
10480 internal::Address* p = reinterpret_cast<internal::Address*>(that.val_);
10481 this->val_ = reinterpret_cast<T*>(V8::CopyGlobalReference(p));
10482 M::Copy(that, this);
10483}
10484
10485template <class T>
10486bool PersistentBase<T>::IsWeak() const {
10487 typedef internal::Internals I;
10488 if (this->IsEmpty()) return false;
10489 return I::GetNodeState(reinterpret_cast<internal::Address*>(this->val_)) ==
10490 I::kNodeStateIsWeakValue;
10491}
10492
10493
10494template <class T>
10495void PersistentBase<T>::Reset() {
10496 if (this->IsEmpty()) return;
10497 V8::DisposeGlobal(reinterpret_cast<internal::Address*>(this->val_));
10498 val_ = nullptr;
10499}

10501

10504void PersistentBase<T>::Reset(Isolate* isolate, const Local<S>& other) {
10505 TYPE_CHECK(T, S);
10506 Reset();
10507 if (other.IsEmpty()) return;
10508 this->val_ = New(isolate, other.val_);
10509}

10512template <class T>

10515 const PersistentBase<S>& other) {
10516 TYPE_CHECK(T, S);
10517 Reset();
10518 if (other.IsEmpty()) return;
10519 this->val_ = New(isolate, other.val_);
10520}

10523template <class T>

10526 P* parameter, typename WeakCallbackInfo<P>::Callback callback,
10527 WeakCallbackType type) {
10528 typedef typename WeakCallbackInfo<void>::Callback Callback;
10529 V8::MakeWeak(reinterpret_cast<internal::Address*>(this->val_), parameter,
10530 reinterpret_cast<Callback>(callback), type);
10531}

10551template <class T>
10552void PersistentBase<T>::SetWrapperClassId(uint16_t class_id) {
10553 typedef internal::Internals I;
10554 if (this->IsEmpty()) return;
10555 internal::Address* obj = reinterpret_cast<internal::Address*>(this->val_);
10556 uint8_t* addr = reinterpret_cast<uint8_t*>(obj) + I::kNodeClassIdOffset;
10557 *reinterpret_cast<uint16_t*>(addr) = class_id;
10558}
10559
10560
10561template <class T>
10562uint16_t PersistentBase<T>::WrapperClassId() const {
10563 typedef internal::Internals I;
10564 if (this->IsEmpty()) return 0;
10565 internal::Address* obj = reinterpret_cast<internal::Address*>(this->val_);
10566 uint8_t* addr = reinterpret_cast<uint8_t*>(obj) + I::kNodeClassIdOffset;
10567 return *reinterpret_cast<uint16_t*>(addr);
10568}
10569
10570template <class T>
10571Global<T>::Global(Global&& other) : PersistentBase<T>(other.val_) {
10572 if (other.val_ != nullptr) {
10573 V8::MoveGlobalReference(reinterpret_cast<internal::Address**>(&other.val_),
10574 reinterpret_cast<internal::Address**>(&this->val_));
10575 other.val_ = nullptr;
10576 }
10577}
10578
10579template <class T>
10580template <class S>
10581Global<T>& Global<T>::operator=(Global<S>&& rhs) {
10582 TYPE_CHECK(T, S);
10583 if (this != &rhs) {
10584 this->Reset();
10585 if (rhs.val_ != nullptr) {
10586 this->val_ = rhs.val_;
10587 V8::MoveGlobalReference(
10588 reinterpret_cast<internal::Address**>(&rhs.val_),
10589 reinterpret_cast<internal::Address**>(&this->val_));
10590 rhs.val_ = nullptr;
10591 }
10592 }
10593 return *this;
10594}
10595
10596template <class T>
10597T* TracedReferenceBase<T>::New(Isolate* isolate, T* that, void* slot,
10598 DestructionMode destruction_mode) {
10599 if (that == nullptr) return nullptr;
10600 internal::Address* p = reinterpret_cast<internal::Address*>(that);
10601 return reinterpret_cast<T*>(V8::GlobalizeTracedReference(
10602 reinterpret_cast<internal::Isolate*>(isolate), p,
10603 reinterpret_cast<internal::Address*>(slot),
10604 destruction_mode == kWithDestructor));
10605}
10606
10607template <class T>
10608void TracedReferenceBase<T>::Reset() {
10609 if (IsEmpty()) return;
10610 V8::DisposeTracedGlobal(reinterpret_cast<internal::Address*>(val_));
10611 val_ = nullptr;
10612}
10613
10614template <class T>
10615template <class S>
10616void TracedGlobal<T>::Reset(Isolate* isolate, const Local<S>& other) {
10617 TYPE_CHECK(T, S);
10618 Reset();
10619 if (other.IsEmpty()) return;
10620 this->val_ = this->New(isolate, other.val_, &this->val_,
10621 TracedReferenceBase<T>::kWithDestructor);
10622}
10623
10624template <class T>
10625template <class S>
10626TracedGlobal<T>& TracedGlobal<T>::operator=(TracedGlobal<S>&& rhs) {
10627 TYPE_CHECK(T, S);
10628 *this = std::move(rhs.template As<T>());
10629 return *this;
10630}
10631
10632template <class T>
10633template <class S>
10634TracedGlobal<T>& TracedGlobal<T>::operator=(const TracedGlobal<S>& rhs) {
10635 TYPE_CHECK(T, S);
10636 *this = rhs.template As<T>();
10637 return *this;
10638}
10639
10640template <class T>
10641TracedGlobal<T>& TracedGlobal<T>::operator=(TracedGlobal&& rhs) {
10642 if (this != &rhs) {
10643 this->Reset();
10644 if (rhs.val_ != nullptr) {
10645 this->val_ = rhs.val_;
10646 V8::MoveTracedGlobalReference(
10647 reinterpret_cast<internal::Address**>(&rhs.val_),
10648 reinterpret_cast<internal::Address**>(&this->val_));
10649 rhs.val_ = nullptr;
10650 }
10651 }
10652 return *this;
10653}
10654
10655template <class T>
10656TracedGlobal<T>& TracedGlobal<T>::operator=(const TracedGlobal& rhs) {
10657 if (this != &rhs) {
10658 this->Reset();
10659 if (rhs.val_ != nullptr) {
10660 V8::CopyTracedGlobalReference(
10661 reinterpret_cast<const internal::Address* const*>(&rhs.val_),
10662 reinterpret_cast<internal::Address**>(&this->val_));
10663 }
10664 }
10665 return *this;
10666}
10667
10668template <class T>
10669template <class S>
10670void TracedReference<T>::Reset(Isolate* isolate, const Local<S>& other) {
10671 TYPE_CHECK(T, S);
10672 Reset();
10673 if (other.IsEmpty()) return;
10674 this->val_ = this->New(isolate, other.val_, &this->val_,
10675 TracedReferenceBase<T>::kWithoutDestructor);
10676}
10677
10678template <class T>
10679template <class S>
10680TracedReference<T>& TracedReference<T>::operator=(TracedReference<S>&& rhs) {
10681 TYPE_CHECK(T, S);
10682 *this = std::move(rhs.template As<T>());
10683 return *this;
10684}
10685
10686template <class T>
10687template <class S>
10688TracedReference<T>& TracedReference<T>::operator=(
10689 const TracedReference<S>& rhs) {
10690 TYPE_CHECK(T, S);
10691 *this = rhs.template As<T>();
10692 return *this;
10693}
10694
10695template <class T>
10696TracedReference<T>& TracedReference<T>::operator=(TracedReference&& rhs) {
10697 if (this != &rhs) {
10698 this->Reset();
10699 if (rhs.val_ != nullptr) {
10700 this->val_ = rhs.val_;
10701 V8::MoveTracedGlobalReference(
10702 reinterpret_cast<internal::Address**>(&rhs.val_),
10703 reinterpret_cast<internal::Address**>(&this->val_));
10704 rhs.val_ = nullptr;
10705 }
10706 }
10707 return *this;
10708}
10709
10710template <class T>
10711TracedReference<T>& TracedReference<T>::operator=(const TracedReference& rhs) {
10712 if (this != &rhs) {
10713 this->Reset();
10714 if (rhs.val_ != nullptr) {
10715 V8::CopyTracedGlobalReference(
10716 reinterpret_cast<const internal::Address* const*>(&rhs.val_),
10717 reinterpret_cast<internal::Address**>(&this->val_));
10718 }
10719 }
10720 return *this;
10721}

10723template <class T>
10724void TracedReferenceBase<T>::SetWrapperClassId(uint16_t class_id) {
10725 typedef internal::Internals I;
10726 if (IsEmpty()) return;
10727 internal::Address* obj = reinterpret_cast<internal::Address*>(val_);
10728 uint8_t* addr = reinterpret_cast<uint8_t*>(obj) + I::kNodeClassIdOffset;
10729 *reinterpret_cast<uint16_t*>(addr) = class_id;
10730}
10731
10732template <class T>
10733uint16_t TracedReferenceBase<T>::WrapperClassId() const {
10734 typedef internal::Internals I;
10735 if (IsEmpty()) return 0;
10736 internal::Address* obj = reinterpret_cast<internal::Address*>(val_);
10737 uint8_t* addr = reinterpret_cast<uint8_t*>(obj) + I::kNodeClassIdOffset;
10738 return *reinterpret_cast<uint16_t*>(addr);
10739}

10752 reinterpret_cast<internal::Address*>(this->val_), parameter, callback);

10755template <typename T>
10756ReturnValue<T>::ReturnValue(internal::Address* slot) : value_(slot) {}

10758template <typename T>
10759template <typename S>
10760void ReturnValue<T>::Set(const Global<S>& handle) {
10761 TYPE_CHECK(T, S);
10762 if (V8_UNLIKELY(handle.IsEmpty())) {
10763 *value_ = GetDefaultValue();
10764 } else {
10765 *value_ = *reinterpret_cast<internal::Address*>(*handle);
10766 }
10767}
10768
10769template <typename T>
10770template <typename S>
10771void ReturnValue<T>::Set(const TracedReferenceBase<S>& handle) {
10772 TYPE_CHECK(T, S);
10773 if (V8_UNLIKELY(handle.IsEmpty())) {
10774 *value_ = GetDefaultValue();
10775 } else {
10776 *value_ = *reinterpret_cast<internal::Address*>(handle.val_);
10777 }
10778}
10779
10780template <typename T>
10781template <typename S>
10782void ReturnValue<T>::Set(const Local<S> handle) {
10783 TYPE_CHECK(T, S);
10784 if (V8_UNLIKELY(handle.IsEmpty())) {
10785 *value_ = GetDefaultValue();
10786 } else {
10787 *value_ = *reinterpret_cast<internal::Address*>(*handle);
10788 }
10789}
10790
10791template<typename T>
10792void ReturnValue<T>::Set(double i) {
10793 TYPE_CHECK(T, Number);
10794 Set(Number::New(GetIsolate(), i));
10795}
10796
10797template<typename T>
10798void ReturnValue<T>::Set(int32_t i) {
10799 TYPE_CHECK(T, Integer);
10800 typedef internal::Internals I;
10801 if (V8_LIKELY(I::IsValidSmi(i))) {
10802 *value_ = I::IntToSmi(i);
10803 return;
10804 }
10805 Set(Integer::New(GetIsolate(), i));
10806}
10807
10808template<typename T>
10809void ReturnValue<T>::Set(uint32_t i) {
10810 TYPE_CHECK(T, Integer);
10811 // Can't simply use INT32_MAX here for whatever reason.
10812 bool fits_into_int32_t = (i & (1U << 31)) == 0;
10813 if (V8_LIKELY(fits_into_int32_t)) {
10814 Set(static_cast<int32_t>(i));
10815 return;
10816 }
10817 Set(Integer::NewFromUnsigned(GetIsolate(), i));
10818}
10819
10820template<typename T>
10821void ReturnValue<T>::Set(bool value) {
10822 TYPE_CHECK(T, Boolean);
10823 typedef internal::Internals I;
10824 int root_index;
10825 if (value) {
10826 root_index = I::kTrueValueRootIndex;
10827 } else {
10828 root_index = I::kFalseValueRootIndex;
10829 }
10830 *value_ = *I::GetRoot(GetIsolate(), root_index);
10831}
10832
10833template<typename T>
10834void ReturnValue<T>::SetNull() {
10835 TYPE_CHECK(T, Primitive);
10836 typedef internal::Internals I;
10837 *value_ = *I::GetRoot(GetIsolate(), I::kNullValueRootIndex);
10838}
10839
10840template<typename T>
10841void ReturnValue<T>::SetUndefined() {
10842 TYPE_CHECK(T, Primitive);
10843 typedef internal::Internals I;
10844 *value_ = *I::GetRoot(GetIsolate(), I::kUndefinedValueRootIndex);
10845}
10846
10847template<typename T>
10848void ReturnValue<T>::SetEmptyString() {
10849 TYPE_CHECK(T, String);
10850 typedef internal::Internals I;
10851 *value_ = *I::GetRoot(GetIsolate(), I::kEmptyStringRootIndex);
10852}
10853
10854template <typename T>
10855Isolate* ReturnValue<T>::GetIsolate() const {
10856 // Isolate is always the pointer below the default value on the stack.
10857 return *reinterpret_cast<Isolate**>(&value_[-2]);
10858}
10859
10860template <typename T>
10861Local<Value> ReturnValue<T>::Get() const {
10862 typedef internal::Internals I;
10863 if (*value_ == *I::GetRoot(GetIsolate(), I::kTheHoleValueRootIndex))
10864 return Local<Value>(*Undefined(GetIsolate()));
10865 return Local<Value>::New(GetIsolate(), reinterpret_cast<Value*>(value_));
10866}
10867
10868template <typename T>
10869template <typename S>
10870void ReturnValue<T>::Set(S* whatever) {
10871 // Uncompilable to prevent inadvertent misuse.
10872 TYPE_CHECK(S*, Primitive);
10873}
10874
10875template <typename T>
10876internal::Address ReturnValue<T>::GetDefaultValue() {
10877 // Default value is always the pointer below value_ on the stack.
10878 return value_[-1];
10879}

10881template <typename T>
10882FunctionCallbackInfo<T>::FunctionCallbackInfo(internal::Address* implicit_args,
10883 internal::Address* values,
10884 int length)
10885 : implicit_args_(implicit_args), values_(values), length_(length) {}
10886
10887template<typename T>
10888Local<Value> FunctionCallbackInfo<T>::operator[](int i) const {
10889 if (i < 0 || length_ <= i) return Local<Value>(*Undefined(GetIsolate()));
10890 return Local<Value>(reinterpret_cast<Value*>(values_ - i));
10891}
10892
10893
10894template<typename T>
10895Local<Object> FunctionCallbackInfo<T>::This() const {
10896 return Local<Object>(reinterpret_cast<Object*>(values_ + 1));
10897}
10898
10899
10900template<typename T>
10901Local<Object> FunctionCallbackInfo<T>::Holder() const {
10902 return Local<Object>(reinterpret_cast<Object*>(
10903 &implicit_args_[kHolderIndex]));
10904}

10909 reinterpret_cast<Value*>(&implicit_args_[kNewTargetIndex]));
10910}
10911
10912template <typename T>
10913Local<Value> FunctionCallbackInfo<T>::Data() const {

10915}

10917
10918template<typename T>

10921}
10922
10923
10924template<typename T>
10925ReturnValue<T> FunctionCallbackInfo<T>::GetReturnValue() const {
10926 return ReturnValue<T>(&implicit_args_[kReturnValueIndex]);
10927}

10929
10930template<typename T>
10931bool FunctionCallbackInfo<T>::IsConstructCall() const {
10932 return !NewTarget()->IsUndefined();
10933}

11050
11051Local<Value> Object::GetInternalField(int index) {
11052#ifndef V8_ENABLE_CHECKS
11053 typedef internal::Address A;
11054 typedef internal::Internals I;
11055 A obj = *reinterpret_cast<A*>(this);
11056 // Fast path: If the object is a plain JSObject, which is the common case, we
11057 // know where to find the internal fields and can return the value directly.
11058 auto instance_type = I::GetInstanceType(obj);
11059 if (instance_type == I::kJSObjectType ||
11060 instance_type == I::kJSApiObjectType ||
11061 instance_type == I::kJSSpecialApiObjectType) {
11062 int offset = I::kJSObjectHeaderSize + (I::kEmbedderDataSlotSize * index);
11063 A value = I::ReadRawField<A>(obj, offset);
11064#ifdef V8_COMPRESS_POINTERS
11065 // We read the full pointer value and then decompress it in order to avoid
11066 // dealing with potential endiannes issues.
11067 value = I::DecompressTaggedAnyField(obj, static_cast<uint32_t>(value));
11068#endif
11069 internal::Isolate* isolate =
11070 internal::IsolateFromNeverReadOnlySpaceObject(obj);
11071 A* result = HandleScope::CreateHandle(isolate, value);
11072 return Local<Value>(reinterpret_cast<Value*>(result));
11073 }
11074#endif
11075 return SlowGetInternalField(index);
11076}
11077
11078
11079void* Object::GetAlignedPointerFromInternalField(int index) {
11080#ifndef V8_ENABLE_CHECKS
11081 typedef internal::Address A;
11082 typedef internal::Internals I;
11083 A obj = *reinterpret_cast<A*>(this);
11084 // Fast path: If the object is a plain JSObject, which is the common case, we
11085 // know where to find the internal fields and can return the value directly.
11086 auto instance_type = I::GetInstanceType(obj);
11087 if (V8_LIKELY(instance_type == I::kJSObjectType ||
11088 instance_type == I::kJSApiObjectType ||
11089 instance_type == I::kJSSpecialApiObjectType)) {
11090 int offset = I::kJSObjectHeaderSize + (I::kEmbedderDataSlotSize * index);
11091 return I::ReadRawField<void*>(obj, offset);
11092 }
11093#endif
11094 return SlowGetAlignedPointerFromInternalField(index);
11095}

11104
11105Local<String> String::Empty(Isolate* isolate) {
11106 typedef internal::Address S;
11107 typedef internal::Internals I;
11108 I::CheckInitialized(isolate);
11109 S* slot = I::GetRoot(isolate, I::kEmptyStringRootIndex);
11110 return Local<String>(reinterpret_cast<String*>(slot));
11111}
11112
11113
11114String::ExternalStringResource* String::GetExternalStringResource() const {
11115 typedef internal::Address A;
11116 typedef internal::Internals I;
11117 A obj = *reinterpret_cast<const A*>(this);
11118
11119 ExternalStringResource* result;
11120 if (I::IsExternalTwoByteString(I::GetInstanceType(obj))) {
11121 void* value = I::ReadRawField<void*>(obj, I::kStringResourceOffset);
11122 result = reinterpret_cast<String::ExternalStringResource*>(value);
11123 } else {
11124 result = GetExternalStringResourceSlow();
11125 }
11126#ifdef V8_ENABLE_CHECKS
11127 VerifyExternalStringResource(result);
11128#endif
11129 return result;
11130}
11131
11132
11133String::ExternalStringResourceBase* String::GetExternalStringResourceBase(
11134 String::Encoding* encoding_out) const {
11135 typedef internal::Address A;
11136 typedef internal::Internals I;
11137 A obj = *reinterpret_cast<const A*>(this);
11138 int type = I::GetInstanceType(obj) & I::kFullStringRepresentationMask;
11139 *encoding_out = static_cast<Encoding>(type & I::kStringEncodingMask);
11140 ExternalStringResourceBase* resource;
11141 if (type == I::kExternalOneByteRepresentationTag ||
11142 type == I::kExternalTwoByteRepresentationTag) {
11143 void* value = I::ReadRawField<void*>(obj, I::kStringResourceOffset);
11144 resource = static_cast<ExternalStringResourceBase*>(value);
11145 } else {
11146 resource = GetExternalStringResourceBaseSlow(encoding_out);
11147 }
11148#ifdef V8_ENABLE_CHECKS
11149 VerifyExternalStringResourceBase(resource, *encoding_out);
11150#endif
11151 return resource;
11152}

11154
11155bool Value::IsUndefined() const {
11156#ifdef V8_ENABLE_CHECKS
11157 return FullIsUndefined();
11158#else
11159 return QuickIsUndefined();
11160#endif
11161}
11162
11163bool Value::QuickIsUndefined() const {
11164 typedef internal::Address A;
11165 typedef internal::Internals I;
11166 A obj = *reinterpret_cast<const A*>(this);
11167 if (!I::HasHeapObjectTag(obj)) return false;
11168 if (I::GetInstanceType(obj) != I::kOddballType) return false;
11169 return (I::GetOddballKind(obj) == I::kUndefinedOddballKind);
11170}
11171
11172
11173bool Value::IsNull() const {
11174#ifdef V8_ENABLE_CHECKS
11175 return FullIsNull();
11176#else
11177 return QuickIsNull();
11178#endif
11179}
11180
11181bool Value::QuickIsNull() const {
11182 typedef internal::Address A;
11183 typedef internal::Internals I;
11184 A obj = *reinterpret_cast<const A*>(this);
11185 if (!I::HasHeapObjectTag(obj)) return false;
11186 if (I::GetInstanceType(obj) != I::kOddballType) return false;
11187 return (I::GetOddballKind(obj) == I::kNullOddballKind);
11188}
11189
11190bool Value::IsNullOrUndefined() const {
11191#ifdef V8_ENABLE_CHECKS
11192 return FullIsNull() || FullIsUndefined();
11193#else
11194 return QuickIsNullOrUndefined();
11195#endif
11196}
11197
11198bool Value::QuickIsNullOrUndefined() const {
11199 typedef internal::Address A;
11200 typedef internal::Internals I;
11201 A obj = *reinterpret_cast<const A*>(this);
11202 if (!I::HasHeapObjectTag(obj)) return false;
11203 if (I::GetInstanceType(obj) != I::kOddballType) return false;
11204 int kind = I::GetOddballKind(obj);
11205 return kind == I::kNullOddballKind || kind == I::kUndefinedOddballKind;
11206}
11207
11208bool Value::IsString() const {
11209#ifdef V8_ENABLE_CHECKS
11210 return FullIsString();
11211#else
11212 return QuickIsString();
11213#endif
11214}
11215
11216bool Value::QuickIsString() const {
11217 typedef internal::Address A;
11218 typedef internal::Internals I;
11219 A obj = *reinterpret_cast<const A*>(this);
11220 if (!I::HasHeapObjectTag(obj)) return false;
11221 return (I::GetInstanceType(obj) < I::kFirstNonstringType);
11222}

11589 if (args_[kShouldThrowOnErrorIndex] !=
11590 I::IntToSmi(I::kInferShouldThrowMode)) {
11591 return args_[kShouldThrowOnErrorIndex] != I::IntToSmi(I::kDontThrow);
11592 }
11593 return v8::internal::ShouldThrowOnError(
11594 reinterpret_cast<v8::internal::Isolate*>(GetIsolate()));
11595}

11656
11657int64_t Isolate::AdjustAmountOfExternalAllocatedMemory(
11658 int64_t change_in_bytes) {
11659 typedef internal::Internals I;
11660 constexpr int64_t kMemoryReducerActivationLimit = 32 * 1024 * 1024;
11661 int64_t* external_memory = reinterpret_cast<int64_t*>(
11662 reinterpret_cast<uint8_t*>(this) + I::kExternalMemoryOffset);
11663 int64_t* external_memory_limit = reinterpret_cast<int64_t*>(
11664 reinterpret_cast<uint8_t*>(this) + I::kExternalMemoryLimitOffset);
11665 int64_t* external_memory_at_last_mc =
11666 reinterpret_cast<int64_t*>(reinterpret_cast<uint8_t*>(this) +
11667 I::kExternalMemoryAtLastMarkCompactOffset);
11668
11669 // Embedders are weird: we see both over- and underflows here. Perform the
11670 // addition with unsigned types to avoid undefined behavior.
11671 const int64_t amount =
11672 static_cast<int64_t>(static_cast<uint64_t>(change_in_bytes) +
11673 static_cast<uint64_t>(*external_memory));
11674 *external_memory = amount;
11675
11676 int64_t allocation_diff_since_last_mc =
11677 static_cast<int64_t>(static_cast<uint64_t>(*external_memory) -
11678 static_cast<uint64_t>(*external_memory_at_last_mc));
11679 // Only check memory pressure and potentially trigger GC if the amount of
11680 // external memory increased.
11681 if (allocation_diff_since_last_mc > kMemoryReducerActivationLimit) {
11682 CheckMemoryPressure();
11683 }
11684
11685 if (change_in_bytes < 0) {
11686 const int64_t lower_limit =
11687 static_cast<int64_t>(static_cast<uint64_t>(*external_memory_limit) +
11688 static_cast<uint64_t>(change_in_bytes));
11689 if (lower_limit > I::kExternalAllocationSoftLimit) {
11690 *external_memory_limit = lower_limit;
11691 }
11692 } else if (change_in_bytes > 0 && amount > *external_memory_limit) {
11693 ReportExternalAllocationLimitReached();
11694 }
11695 return *external_memory;
11696}
11697
11698Local<Value> Context::GetEmbedderData(int index) {
11699#ifndef V8_ENABLE_CHECKS
11700 typedef internal::Address A;
11701 typedef internal::Internals I;
11702 A ctx = *reinterpret_cast<const A*>(this);
11703 A embedder_data =
11704 I::ReadTaggedPointerField(ctx, I::kNativeContextEmbedderDataOffset);
11705 int value_offset =
11706 I::kEmbedderDataArrayHeaderSize + (I::kEmbedderDataSlotSize * index);
11707 A value = I::ReadRawField<A>(embedder_data, value_offset);
11708#ifdef V8_COMPRESS_POINTERS
11709 // We read the full pointer value and then decompress it in order to avoid
11710 // dealing with potential endiannes issues.
11711 value =
11712 I::DecompressTaggedAnyField(embedder_data, static_cast<uint32_t>(value));
11713#endif
11714 internal::Isolate* isolate = internal::IsolateFromNeverReadOnlySpaceObject(
11715 *reinterpret_cast<A*>(this));
11716 A* result = HandleScope::CreateHandle(isolate, value);
11717 return Local<Value>(reinterpret_cast<Value*>(result));
11718#else
11719 return SlowGetEmbedderData(index);
11720#endif
11721}
11722
11723
11724void* Context::GetAlignedPointerFromEmbedderData(int index) {
11725#ifndef V8_ENABLE_CHECKS
11726 typedef internal::Address A;
11727 typedef internal::Internals I;
11728 A ctx = *reinterpret_cast<const A*>(this);
11729 A embedder_data =
11730 I::ReadTaggedPointerField(ctx, I::kNativeContextEmbedderDataOffset);
11731 int value_offset =
11732 I::kEmbedderDataArrayHeaderSize + (I::kEmbedderDataSlotSize * index);
11733 return I::ReadRawField<void*>(embedder_data, value_offset);
11734#else
11735 return SlowGetAlignedPointerFromEmbedderData(index);
11736#endif
11737}
11738
11739template <class T>
11740MaybeLocal<T> Context::GetDataFromSnapshotOnce(size_t index) {
11741 T* data = reinterpret_cast<T*>(GetDataFromSnapshotOnce(index));
11742 if (data) internal::PerformCastCheck(data);
11743 return Local<T>(data);
11744}

11750 return AddData(context, *p);
11751}
